class Solution:
    def numberOfSequence(self, n: int, sick: List[int]) -> int:
        MOD = 10**9 + 7
        sick_set = set(sick)
        dp = [0]*n
        dp[0] = 1
        for i in range(1, n):
            if i not in sick_set:
                dp[i] = dp[i-1]
                if i-2 >= 0 and i-2 not in sick_set:
                    dp[i] += dp[i-2]
                    dp[i] %= MOD
        return dp[-1]
```

This solution uses dynamic programming to solve the problem. The dp array stores the number of possible infection sequences up to the current position. For each position i, if it is not infected, the number of possible sequences is the same as the number of possible sequences at position i-1. If position i-2 is not infected and position i is not infected, then we can add the number of possible sequences at position i-2 to the number of possible sequences at position i-1. This is because we can choose to infect position i first or position i-1 first. The time complexity of this solution is O(n) and the space complexity is O(n).

